The Chronicle Ricky Zililo, Senior Sports Reporter HIGHLANDERS defender Peter Muduhwa is back in country following a brief unsuccessful stint with Tanzania giants Simba SC. Muduhwa immediately got down to business, undergoing Covid-19 and medical tests with the Bulawayo giants on Tuesday morning. The defence stalwart’s six-month loan deal with the Tanzanians was terminated halfway through and he returned from Dar-es-Salaam without kicking a ball. <img class="wp-image-540869 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/04/med-mhango.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/04/med-mhango.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/04/med-mhango-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Winston Mhango undergoing his medical “We are not taking chances. As we continue with our preseason preparations, the players are undergoing medical tests. Football is coming back,” Bosso wrote on their official social media pages, with pictures of players undergoing tests. <img class="wp-image-540875 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/04/med-Makaruse.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/04/med-Makaruse.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/04/med-Makaruse-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Makaruse having his medical Also pictured doing his medical with Muduhwa are new signings, midfielder Winston Mhango and striker Lynnoth Chikuhwa, and winger Godfrey Makaruse. <img class="wp-image-540872 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/04/med-Chikuhwa.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/04/med-Chikuhwa.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/04/med-Chikuhwa-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Chikuhwa having his medical The return of the 27-year-old Muduhwa, who can also play as a right-back or defensive midfielder, will give Bosso a huge boost ahead of Sunday’s Independence Cup match against Dynamos. – @ZililoR 